body_html:
Hello @wangyongqi We have updated both the stack overflow links. Seems bytebuffer issue exists in all tensorflow-lite versions except for the nightly build(org.tensorflow:tensorflow-lite:0.0.0-nightly). But on using the nightly build, we are facing a different issue.

java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: Internal error: Failed to run on the given Interpreter: tensorflow/lite/kernels/depthwise_conv.cc:99 params->depth_multiplier * SizeOfDimension(input, 3) != SizeOfDimension(filter, 3) (0 != 32)Node number 30 (DEPTHWISE_CONV_2D) failed to prepare.

This issue is with respect to our model (Mobilenetv2 - DeeplabV3)

Hello @wangyongqi  We have updated both the stack overflow links. Seems bytebuffer issue exists in all tensorflow-lite versions except for the nightly build(org.tensorflow:tensorflow-lite:0.0.0-nightly). But on using the nightly build, we are facing a different issue. 

`java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: Internal error: Failed to run on the given Interpreter: tensorflow/lite/kernels/depthwise_conv.cc:99 params->depth_multiplier * SizeOfDimension(input, 3) != SizeOfDimension(filter, 3) (0 != 32)Node number 30 (DEPTHWISE_CONV_2D) failed to prepare.`

This issue is with respect to our model (Mobilenetv2 - DeeplabV3)
